{
    "name": "Gibbering Mouther",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Disgusting, loathsome, and hungry\u2014these are the only words that properly describe the gibbering mouther. A foul beast that lurks in underground caves, sewers, and nightmares, mouthers have no societal, ecological or religious significance other than their ability to drive those that listen to them mad. Some scholars believe that gibbering mouthers are a lesser variant of the much more dangerous shoggoth, while others theorize they are a punishment by some powerful being or deity inflicted on those who have offended it."
        }
    ],
